==English==

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|UK}} {{IPA|/əˌfoː(ɹ)ˈmɛn.ʃənd/}}, {{SAMPA|/@%fo:(r)"mEn.S@nd/}}

===Adjective===
{{en-adj|-}}

# [[previously|Previously]] [[mention]]ed.
#* ''The PA system broadcast a long list of names in the morning, but it wasn't until later that they requested the '''aforementioned''' students report to the health clinic.''

====Usage notes====
When it modifies a noun phrase, it is generally preceded by the definite article ''[[the]]'', and the combination functions as a [[determiner]] rather than a simple adjective. You can put it before a cardinal like ''the '''aforementioned''' two papers'' instead of ''the two aforementioned papers''.

